(36, 'dtp entertainment AG', 'http://www.dtp-ag.com/', NULL, '2008-04-01 01:32:52', 124),
(37, 'Radon Labs GmbH', NULL, '<h2>Overview</h2><p>Founded in  Berlin, Germany, Radon Labs (formerly known as TerraTools) has developed an assortment ofxA0  RPGs, Simulations, Adventure, Action, Side Scrolling and Strategy games boasting an assortment of Awards. Key people as of 2010 were Managing Directors Bernd Beyreuther and Andre Blechschmidt, it has been recorded that the independent developer had 90  employees in both its headquarters and branch studio in Halle-Leipzig.xA0</p>Radon Lab is also accredited to have developed the Nebula Device an open source 3D engine.xA0<br/><h2>Bankruptcy and Acquisition</h2>In May 2010 Radon Labs filed for bankruptcy due to it''s financial concerns and as a result was acquired by <a data-ref-id="3010-7241" href="/bigpoint-games/3010-7241" slug="bigpoint-games"> BigPoint GmbH</a>.xA0Consequently, Bernd Beyreuther and Andre Blechschmidt along with 33 Radon Labs employees had moved to BigPoint''s newly formed branch in Berlin to work on Browser-based games.xA0', '2008-04-01 01:32:52', 129),
(39, 'Agetec, Inc.', 'http://www.agetec.com/', '<h2>Overview</h2><p>Agetec (ASCII Games Entertainment Technology) is a California-based game publisher that picks up the North American release rights to Japanese titles and has them localized for distribution to their American audience. The company was created as a subsidiary of <a href="/ascii-entertainment-software-inc/3010-761" data-ref-id="3010-761">ASCII Entertainment Software</a>, itself a western branch of the Japanese <a href="/ascii-corporation/3010-805" data-ref-id="3010-805">ASCII Corporation</a>.</p><h2>Releases</h2><p>The majority of Agetec''s release catalog is filled with relatively obscure, niche titles such as the RPG Maker series. However, they have on occasion stepped in to publish more noteworthy titles such as <a href="/space-channel-5-special-edition/3030-10373" data-ref-id="3030-10373">Space Channel 5 Special Edition</a>, <a href="/the-king-of-fighters-99/3030-5964" data-ref-id="3030-5964"> King of Fighters ''99</a>, and several <a href="/armored-core/3025-35" data-ref-id="3025-35">Armored Core</a> titles.</p><p>The company has become less prolific the 2010s, focusing on smaller downloadable titles on platforms like the 3DS eShop. Their most recent new title announcement was a move into mobile with the iOS version of <a href="/banshee-s-last-cry/3030-28241" data-ref-id="3030-28241">Kamaitachi no Yoru</a> in 2012, however nothing appears to have come of this and the game was eventually released by <a href="/aksys-games/3010-932" data-ref-id="3010-932">Aksys Games</a> instead as <a href="/banshee-s-last-cry/3030-28241" data-ref-id="3030-28241">Banshee''s Last Cry</a> in 2014.</p>', '2008-04-01 01:32:52', 80),
(41, 'Max Design GesMBH', NULL, '<p>xA0<br/>Max Design was founded in 1991 by brothers <a data-ref-id="3040-26726" href="/albert-lasser/3040-26726" slug="albert-lasser">     Albert</a> and <a data-ref-id="3040-26728" href="/martin-lasser/3040-26728" slug="martin-lasser">      Martin Lasser,</a> as well as <a data-ref-id="3040-26727" href="/wilfried-reiter/3040-26727" slug="wilfried-reiter">    Wilfried Reiter.</a> The company found success by developing successful economical simulation games, such as <a data-ref-id="3030-1203" href="/the-patrician/3030-1203" slug="the-patrician">   The Patrician</a>, <a data-ref-id="3030-12712" href="/1869/3030-12712" slug="1869">  1869</a>, or the <a data-ref-id="3025-856" href="/anno/3025-856" slug="anno"> Anno series</a>. After 12 years, Max Design decided to close down in 2004, stating that the need for a reorientation prompted the "permanent break" of the studio. The founders of Max Design however did not stay away from the game business for long and founded Red Monkeys in 2006.</p>', '2008-04-01 01:32:53', 107),
(42, 'Shrapnel Games, Inc.', 'http://www.shrapnelgames.com/', NULL, '2008-04-01 01:32:53', 115),
(43, 'Tiny Hero Game Studios', NULL, NULL, '2008-04-01 01:32:53', 119),
(44, 'Fox Interactive', 'http://www.fox.com/', '<p>A subdivision of <a data-ref-id="3010-2240" href="/20th-century-fox/3010-2240" slug="20th-century-fox"> 20th Century Fox</a>, Fox Interactive developed and published games based on licenses of films developed by the parent company 20th Century Fox. The most successful game series based on 20th Century Fox franchises were <a data-ref-id="3025-26" href="/aliens-vs-predator/3025-26" slug="aliens-vs-predator"> Alien vs. Predator</a>, <a data-ref-id="3025-283" href="/the-simpsons/3025-283" slug="the-simpsons"> The Simpsons</a> and <a data-ref-id="3025-149" href="/die-hard/3025-149" slug="die-hard"> Die Hard</a>. Fox Interactive also released a handful of sport games of popular American sports such as <a data-ref-id="3030-27614" href="/fox-sports-nba-basketball-2000/3030-27614" slug="fox-sports-nba-basketball-2000"> NBA Basketball</a> and <a data-ref-id="3030-17681" href="/nhl-championship-2000/3030-17681" slug="nhl-championship-2000"> NHL Championship</a>. In addition to a few original titles such as the <a data-ref-id="3005-2564" href="/croc/3005-2564" slug="croc"> Croc</a> series and <a data-ref-id="3030-18911" href="/the-operative-no-one-lives-forever/3030-18911" slug="the-operative-no-one-lives-forever"> No One Lives Forever</a>. In early 2003, Fox Interactive was acquired by <a data-ref-id="3010-6398" href="/vivendi-games/3010-6398" slug="vivendi-games"> Vivendi Universal</a>.</p>', '2008-04-01 01:32:53', 99),
(45, 'Hyperbole Studios', 'http://www.hyperbole.com/', NULL, '2008-04-01 01:32:53', 97),
(46, 'Sony Computer Entertainment Europe', 'http://eu.playstation.com/', '<h2>Overview</h2><p>Sony Computer Entertainment Europe is one of the three main divisions of Sony Computer Entertainment, alongside <a href="/sony-computer-entertainment-america/3010-313" data-ref-id="3010-313">SCE America</a>, and SCE Japan-Asia.</p><p>While headquartered in and named for Europe, SCEE also covers SCE''s business in Australia, Africa, and parts of Aisa (including India and the middle east). This arrangement was born out of these countries historical adoption of the European PAL TV standard, and has continued even after HDTV and HDMI has made the distinction less important.</p><h2>Corporate Leaders</h2><h3>Current</h3><ul><li><a href="/jim-ryan/3040-45779" data-ref-id="3040-45779">Jim Ryan</a> - President and CEO (2011-)</li><li><a href="/michael-denny/3040-72" data-ref-id="3040-72">Michael Denny</a> - Vice President of WWS Europe (2008-)</li></ul><h3>Former</h3><ul><li>Chris Deering - Founder, President and CEO (1995-2005)</li><li><a href="/david-reeves/3040-46990" data-ref-id="3040-46990">David Reeves</a> - President and CEO (2005-2009)</li><li><a href="/andrew-house/3040-665" data-ref-id="3040-665">Andrew House</a> - President and CEO (2009-2011)</li></ul><p> </p>', '2008-04-01 01:32:53', 111),
(47, 'ReadySoft Incorporated', NULL, NULL, '2008-04-01 01:32:54', 125),
(48, 'Philips Interactive Media, Inc.', NULL, NULL, '2008-04-01 01:32:54', 148),
(49, 'Don Bluth Ltd.', NULL, '<p>The company behind games such as <a data-ref-id="3030-23" href="/dragons-lair/3030-23" slug="dragons-lair">Dragon''s Lai</a>r and <a data-ref-id="3030-463" href="/space-ace/3030-463" slug="space-ace">Space Ace</a>.</p>', '2008-04-01 01:32:54', 117),
(50, 'Digital Leisure Inc.', 'http://www.digitalleisure.com/', NULL, '2008-04-01 01:32:54', 90),
(51, 'Positech Computing Ltd.', 'http://www.positech.co.uk/', '<span>Positech Games was founded in 1997 by ex-Lionhead Studios programmer Cliff Harris. Positech specializes in cheap downloadable PC games, with their biggest being the Democracy and Kudos series. Democracy is a political strategy game where the player must manage a nation as the president or prime minister. While Kudos is very similar to EA''s The Sims franchise. Positech Games is the maker of very complex strategy games that appeal to a hardcore gamer fan base, unlike many of their competitors in the cheap downloadable games market who design casual puzzle and arcade games.</span>', '2008-04-01 01:32:54', 114),
(52, 'Deep Silver', 'http://www.deepsilver.net/', '<p>Deep Silver (part of <a data-ref-id="3010-3830" href="/koch-media/3010-3830" slug="koch-media">Koch Media</a>) recently bought up <a data-ref-id="3025-386" href="/saints-row/3025-386" slug="saints-row">Saints Row</a> and <a data-ref-id="3025-1749" href="/metro/3025-1749" slug="metro">Metro</a> franchises during <a data-ref-id="3010-15" href="/thq/3010-15" slug="thq">THQ</a>''s assets auction.</p>', '2008-04-01 01:32:54', 123),
(53, 'Pluto 13 GmbH', 'http://www.pluto13.de/', '<h2>Change to Pluto 13 </h2>Originally known as Piranha Bytes, the company was founded in 1997 in Ruhrgebiet, Germany, by five former members of <a data-ref-id="3010-1902" href="/greenwood-entertainment/3010-1902"> Greenwood Entertainment Software</a>. In 1999, the company became a subsidiary of Phenomedia AG, a German publishing company that went public during the dot-com boom. Shortly after Piranha Bytes released their first game, <a data-ref-id="3030-1982" href="/gothic/3030-1982">        Gothic</a>, in late 2001, Phenomedia went into insolvency proceedings after allegations that several executives had falsified balance sheets, for which several served prison sentences for securities fraud. In response, Piranha Bytes executed a management buyout to sever itself from Phenomedia, changing their name in Pluto 13.<br /><br /><h2>Split With JoWood </h2>In 2007, Piranha Bytes split with its long time publisher, <a data-ref-id="3010-54" href="/jowood-productions-software-ag/3010-54">             JoWood Productions</a>. In the split, JoWood retained publishing rights to the company''s <a data-ref-id="3025-672" href="/gothic/3025-672">            Gothic </a>series, including future releases. This lead to Pluto''s next title, <a data-ref-id="3030-23081" href="/risen/3030-23081">           Risen</a>, not being a game in the franchise, even though it highly resembles the Gothic series in using the same engine and storytelling mechanics, even to the point of being commonly referred to as Gothic 4.', '2008-04-01 01:32:54', 133),
